{"parse":{"title":"William Elvis Sloan","pageid":20644288,"revid":789485098,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:William-elvis-sloan.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"William-elvis-sloan.jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/77/William-elvis-sloan.jpg/220px-William-elvis-sloan.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"282\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/77/William-elvis-sloan.jpg/330px-William-elvis-sloan.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/77/William-elvis-sloan.jpg/440px-William-elvis-sloan.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2086\" data-file-height=\"2672\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:William-elvis-sloan.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div></div></div></div>\n<p><b>William Elvis Sloan I</b> (October 1867 \u2013 June 25, 1961) invented the <a href=\"/wiki/Flushometer\" title=\"Flushometer\">Flushometer</a> flushing mechanism for toilets and urinals. It is installed in millions of commercial, institutional and industrial restrooms worldwide.<sup id=\"cite_ref-wholesale_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-wholesale-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-bio_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bio-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=William_Elvis_Sloan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Liberty,_Missouri\" title=\"Liberty, Missouri\">Liberty, Missouri</a> in October 1867.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bio_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bio-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He was an apprentice pipe fitter in Missouri then moved to <a href=\"/wiki/Chicago,_Illinois\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Chicago, Illinois\">Chicago, Illinois</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-wholesale_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-wholesale-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He married Bertha Moore (1874-?) in 1898 in <a href=\"/wiki/Chicago,_Illinois\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Chicago, Illinois\">Chicago, Illinois</a> and they had a child, Edith Marie Sloan (1913-?).\n</p><p>In 1906, he founded <a href=\"/wiki/Sloan_Valve_Company\" title=\"Sloan Valve Company\">Sloan Valve Company</a>, which is now headquartered in <a href=\"/wiki/Franklin_Park,_Illinois\" title=\"Franklin Park, Illinois\">Franklin Park, Illinois</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bio_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bio-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>He died on June 25, 1961 in <a href=\"/wiki/Chicago,_Illinois\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Chicago, Illinois\">Chicago, Illinois</a> and was buried in <a href=\"/wiki/Oak_Park,_Illinois\" title=\"Oak Park, Illinois\">Oak Park, Illinois</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Legacy\">Legacy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=William_Elvis_Sloan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Legacy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>With the exception of a period of time in the 1940s and early 1950s, Sloan Valve has been under the leadership of W.E. Sloan\u2019s descendants. He had a grandson William Elvis Sloan II (1941&#8211;2001).<sup id=\"cite_ref-obit_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-obit-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=William_Elvis_Sloan&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-wholesale-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-wholesale_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-wholesale_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20141204143950/http://www.thewholesaler.com/sept_06/sloan_anniversary.php\">\"Sloan Valve Continues To Build On Strong Foundation\"</a>. The Wholesaler<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-08-04</span></span>. <q>Early in his career, Sloan was an apprentice pipe fitter in his native Missouri before moving to Chicago and working as a foreman, superintendent and, later, an independent contractor. His experiences and self-study led Sloan to a lifelong interest in inventing \u2014 over his lifetime, Sloan was credited with 64 inventions.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Sloan+Valve+Continues+To+Build+On+Strong+Foundation&amp;rft.pub=The+Wholesaler&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20141204143950%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.thewholesaler.com%2Fsept_06%2Fsloan_anniversary.php&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWilliam+Elvis+Sloan\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-bio-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-bio_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-bio_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-bio_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20090315111945/http://www.sloanvalve.com/index_331_ENU_HTML.htm\">\"William Elvis Sloan (1867-1961)\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Sloan_Valve_Company\" title=\"Sloan Valve Company\">Sloan Valve Company</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.sloanvalve.com/index_331_ENU_HTML.htm\">the original</a> on March 15, 2009<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-08-04</span></span>. <q>The inventor of the Flushometer and founder of Sloan Valve Company was born in Liberty, Missouri. After serving as an apprentice pipe fitter, he traveled to Chicago and became a foreman, a superintendent, and finally, an independent contractor.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=William+Elvis+Sloan+%281867-1961%29&amp;rft.pub=Sloan+Valve+Company&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.sloanvalve.com%2Findex_331_ENU_HTML.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWilliam+Elvis+Sloan\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.newspapers.com/clip/6644819/william_elvis_sloan_i_18671961/\">\"Board Chairman Dies\"</a>. <i>Holland Evening Sentinel</i>. June 27, 1961  &#8211; via <a href=\"/wiki/Newspapers.com\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Newspapers.com\">Newspapers.com</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Holland+Evening+Sentinel&amp;rft.atitle=Board+Chairman+Dies&amp;rft.date=1961-06-27&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newspapers.com%2Fclip%2F6644819%2Fwilliam_elvis_sloan_i_18671961%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWilliam+Elvis+Sloan\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-obit-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-obit_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/chicagotribune/access/77024409.html?dids=77024409:77024409&amp;FMT=ABS&amp;FMTS=ABS:FT&amp;date=Aug+05%2C+2001&amp;author=&amp;pub=Chicago+Tribune&amp;desc=WILLIAM+ELVIS+SLOAN+II%2C+60&amp;pqatl=google\">\"William Elvis Sloan II, 60\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Chicago_Tribune\" title=\"Chicago Tribune\">Chicago Tribune</a></i>. August 5, 2001<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-08-04</span></span>. <q>William Elvis Sloan II, 60, an executive at Sloan Valve Co. in Franklin Park, died Wednesday, Aug. 1, in his Addison home of a heart attack. Born and raised in River Forest, Mr. Sloan built a 44-year career with the company, a manufacturer of plumbing products that was founded by his grandfather in Chicago. Starting at age 16, Mr. ...</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Chicago+Tribune&amp;rft.atitle=William+Elvis+Sloan+II%2C+60&amp;rft.date=2001-08-05&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fpqasb.pqarchiver.com%2Fchicagotribune%2Faccess%2F77024409.html%3Fdids%3D77024409%3A77024409%26FMT%3DABS%26FMTS%3DABS%3AFT%26date%3DAug%2B05%252C%2B2001%26author%3D%26pub%3DChicago%2BTribune%26desc%3DWILLIAM%2BELVIS%2BSLOAN%2BII%252C%2B60%26pqatl%3Dgoogle&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AWilliam+Elvis+Sloan\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1341\nCached time: 20180909210137\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.092 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.113 seconds\nPreprocessor visi